begin_memory_text: We talked about basic things about ourselves—I talked about how I was from the Bay Area, he talked about how he was from New York, and we asked each other whether we've visited West and the East Coast, respectively.
middle_memory_text: We talked about what we do/our line of work. I learned that he was an accountant who also practiced law. He gave me advice about law school should I ever want to attend & explained the value of having a law degree as an accountant.
end_memory_text: We talked about our family backgrounds and how immigration of our ancestors contributed to where we are today. I learned a lot about his background with his family being Italian.
rest_of_day_open: I see it going fine, not really different from any other week. I anticipate that I will be busy as usual with work during the weekdays, but I'll be sure to set aside some time to take a break. Without repeating myself from the last survey, I do plan on voting this week as well which is something I look forward to.
critical_positive: I think we both came to the conversation with different strengths—my conversation partner was very intellectual and seemed to have a lot of knowledge on a wide array of topics, which provided for interesting material. On the other hand, I think I was a very good listener and knew when and how to engage positively in the conversation.
critical_negative: I do think the fact that we came from very different backgrounds did make it a little difficult to find common ground. For example, he's from New York, I'm from California, he's many years out of college and has an established career whereas I'm still a student, etc. That being said, it was interesting to be engaging with someone of a demographic that I likely would not have much interaction with at this stage in my life.

begin_memory_text: My webcam didn't want to work for some reason.  At first it didn't give a picture, then a picture but no sound.  He could see me and I could hear him.  It was a bit of a mess.  Finally, my end got working and we had a good laugh about the kerfuffle.  He also told me that he had trouble on a prior chat using Chrome.  He also introduced himself as Jack from the Bay Area.  He's in his third year of college, but taking a semester off because of COVID-19.
middle_memory_text: Around the middle I believe we started talking about the Salton Sea and Aral Sea.  (he was surprised I knew about the Salton Sea when most people around him in California have no clue.)  This was in the context of where he is being better versus southern California, which we both agreed was kind of a desert with no water.  And then we talked about Las Vegas which is in a literal desert.
end_memory_text: I believe we talked about our respective backgrounds.  His 4x great grandfather came over from Sweden around 1890 and settled in the Bay Area.  His family has been in that little area ever since, in the same places, in the same schools, etc.  I then talked about my family history and the fun mess that is by comparison.
rest_of_day_open: So I have a tax deadline on Thursday.  I squared away a bunch of outstanding returns this weekend, but still have a good two or three big ones to get out of the way that will probably eat up a good portion of the next couple of days.  Beyond that, I have an important phone call tomorrow about a VERY irritating real estate deal in Brighton Beach.
critical_positive: He seemed interested in what I was saying.  I reckon we're both good listeners, so that helped.  But I do feel like I did a lot more of the talking and him more of the listening.  That said, I believe he was listening and was generally interested and friendly.  I figure we're both nice guys ultimately and just got along, even if we didn't have a whole lot in common.
critical_negative: So we don't have a whole lot in common.  He's a west coast guy and I'm very much not.  He's in college; I'm a 34 year old lawyer-CPA who's been in private practice for 8 years.  There's a gulf there.  So finding stuff to talk about was a little bit harder as there was something of an informational imbalance owing to our different stations in life (basically, I'm a decade plus older, so I'm just going to generally have more experience).
